definition.value: An L-altrofuranose that has beta configuration at the anomeric position.
A glycosyl glycoside consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and D-galactopyranose residues joined by a (1->1) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-D-glucopyranose and D-galactopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylglucose consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose and D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
